  "StockRole": "Juggernaut & Heavy Cavalry",
  "YangsThoughts": "The Mauler has had a lack of new variants since the Jihad. LAW's developmental experimentation in the late 3060s sought to perfect a new weapons suite focused on medium ranges while  improving the armor to suit an assault 'Mech. It did not fare well. As in a prior attempt to update the BattleMech most liked variant — 3062's MAL-3R — the Mauler's volatile CASE had to be discarded to accommodate new autocannon solutions, thereby undermining the quest for increased resilience. Increased armor mass required the use of a bulky endo-steel structure, reducing internal space, and allowing only a small cockpit. This aggregation of compromises eventually resulted in the flawed MAL-1KX, many of its shortcomings were never fixed, as the final production version that eventually became the MAL-1K was instead based on the MAL-1R.",
